1
00:00:00,660 --> 00:00:03,320
(The warm vibe of spring makes the cast members smile.)

2
00:00:03,353 --> 00:00:04,852
- Mieum...
- What should it be?

3
00:00:04,853 --> 00:00:05,922
- and siot.
- Come again?

4
00:00:05,923 --> 00:00:06,907
Magic.

5
00:00:07,653 --> 00:00:08,893
- What are they doing?
- Art.

6
00:00:09,153 --> 00:00:09,870
Meditation.

7
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,730
Gourmandise.

8
00:00:12,573 --> 00:00:14,813
Oh, gosh. I envy you, Kyung Hoon.

9
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:16,492
- Why?
- Because your wife is the director,

10
00:00:16,493 --> 00:00:17,963
you do the opening with Ho Dong.

11
00:00:19,237 --> 00:00:20,836
- This is so unfair.
- My gosh.

12
00:00:20,861 --> 00:00:21,931
- But...
- Exactly.

13
00:00:22,092 --> 00:00:22,902
Soo Geun.

14
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:24,872
- According to Kyung Hoon, - Yes?

15
00:00:24,873 --> 00:00:28,043
just as exercising is important to keep our bodies healthy,

16
00:00:28,450 --> 00:00:30,520
- we also need to train our brains.
- That's right.

17
00:00:30,743 --> 00:00:32,142
In that case, Ho Dong, you should train your brain hard...

18
00:00:32,143 --> 00:00:33,582
because you have such a big brain.

19
00:00:33,583 --> 00:00:34,742
Oh, goodness.

20
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:36,252
- That's right.
- He said...

21
00:00:36,253 --> 00:00:37,712
- we should train our brains.
- He's right about that.

22
00:00:37,713 --> 00:00:39,822
- It helps to prevent dementia too.
- Right.

23
00:00:39,823 --> 00:00:41,693
- Yes.
- Hey, guys...

24
00:00:42,823 --> 00:00:43,823
(Tough)

25
00:00:43,823 --> 00:00:44,823
Ready, go.

26
00:00:44,824 --> 00:00:46,393
(Heave-ho, here we go)

27
00:00:48,093 --> 00:00:50,062
(The transfer students enter while singing a sailing song?)

28
00:00:50,063 --> 00:00:51,193
That startled me. What's going on?

29
00:00:53,363 --> 00:00:54,433
Here they come!

30
00:00:55,273 --> 00:00:57,832
(They safely arrived at Men on a Mission Port.)

31
00:00:57,833 --> 00:00:59,342
Look how much Tae Yeon has grown.

32
00:00:59,343 --> 00:01:00,472
- What's going on?
- One, two, three, four,

33
00:01:00,473 --> 00:01:02,173
- five, six, seven...
- Where did you transfer from?

34
00:01:02,943 --> 00:01:06,082
Hi. We are...

35
00:01:06,083 --> 00:01:07,843
from Queens Of Active Trot Singers To Touch Your Hearts High School.

36
00:01:08,023 --> 00:01:09,993
I'm Hong Ji Yun, the prettiest one.

37
00:01:10,273 --> 00:01:12,842
I'm Kim Tae Yeon, the life of the party.

38
00:01:12,883 --> 00:01:14,783
I'm Solji, the cutie pie.

39
00:01:16,153 --> 00:01:17,792
I'm absolutely the thinking type...

40
00:01:17,793 --> 00:01:19,662
who looks like I'm made of stone. I'm Ku Su Kyung.

41
00:01:19,663 --> 00:01:22,093
I'm Kang Hye Yeon, the comedienne of the group.

42
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:25,000
I'm Su Yeon, the golden youngest member!

43
00:01:25,803 --> 00:01:27,762
- It's nice to meet you all.
- Welcome!

44
00:01:27,763 --> 00:01:28,772
It's so nice to meet you all.

45
00:01:28,773 --> 00:01:30,402
Tae Yeon, you've grown so tall.

46
00:01:30,403 --> 00:01:33,002
You're even taller than Ji Yun, who's right next to you.

47
00:01:33,003 --> 00:01:35,473
- Tae Yeon, what happened?
- It's been ages.

48
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:38,802
This is Tae Yeon's third time being on this show.

49
00:01:38,843 --> 00:01:40,637
- That's right.
- She's grown so tall.

50
00:01:40,823 --> 00:01:43,353
Right. I'm 163cm tall now.

51
00:01:43,813 --> 00:01:44,882
- She's grown so much.
- Oh, my.

52
00:01:44,883 --> 00:01:46,722
Were you in kindergarten the last time you were here?

53
00:01:46,723 --> 00:01:49,422
- How old were you then?
- No, I was ten.

54
00:01:49,423 --> 00:01:51,052
- How old are you now?
- I'm 15 now.

55
00:01:51,053 --> 00:01:52,522
- Oh, my.
- You've become calm.

56
00:01:52,523 --> 00:01:54,162
You really made a scene the last time you were here.

57
00:01:54,163 --> 00:01:56,092
- Right.
- How was I?

58
00:01:56,093 --> 00:01:58,432
- You were quite playful, you know.
- Was it five years ago?

59
00:01:58,433 --> 00:01:59,433
- That's right.
- The last time you were here,

60
00:01:59,434 --> 00:02:01,263
- She argued with the older guests.
- she argued...

61
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:05,343
(Tae Yeon's 2nd time on the show 5 years ago)

62
00:02:06,673 --> 00:02:10,373
(She was unusually energetic, even for her 2nd time here.)

63
00:02:10,843 --> 00:02:14,743
(She stepped into the center and showcased her dance skills.)

64
00:02:15,183 --> 00:02:16,752
(The 10-year-old Tae Yeon completely owned the classroom.)

65
00:02:16,753 --> 00:02:18,822
- She wasn't outshone by anyone.
- That's right.

66
00:02:18,823 --> 00:02:19,982
You seem so calm now.

67
00:02:19,983 --> 00:02:22,452
You don't even speak so much. Are you being quiet on purpose?

68
00:02:22,453 --> 00:02:23,822
That's because I'm shy.

69
00:02:23,823 --> 00:02:25,622
You are shy? You?

70
00:02:25,623 --> 00:02:28,092
- I'll warm up as time goes by.
- She's become mature.

71
00:02:28,093 --> 00:02:30,032
- She's become too mature.
- All right. I mean...

72
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:31,332
The last time you were here,

73
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:33,262
- you were Su Yeon's age, right?
- She was ten back then.

74
00:02:33,263 --> 00:02:34,362
- Right, she was Su Yeon's age.
- You were younger than her, right?

75
00:02:34,363 --> 00:02:36,373
- I was younger than she is now.
- This is your third time here.

76
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:39,502
Weren't you around Su Yeon's age during your second visit?

77
00:02:39,503 --> 00:02:41,272
- I was 11 then.
- Right.

78
00:02:41,273 --> 00:02:42,372
- She didn't talk in that tone.
- She was younger than Su Yeon.

79
00:02:42,373 --> 00:02:43,512
Right, you didn't talk in this tone.

80
00:02:43,513 --> 00:02:44,972
- You didn't, as far as I remember.
- She's being shy.

81
00:02:44,973 --> 00:02:46,842
She was like, "I want to talk too!"

82
00:02:46,843 --> 00:02:48,582
I was 11 the last time I was here.

83
00:02:48,583 --> 00:02:50,552
You were 11, right?

84
00:02:50,553 --> 00:02:53,182
- She's become a little bit shy.
- Tae Yeon... Right.

85
00:02:53,183 --> 00:02:54,352
As we talked about how she was at 11,

86
00:02:54,353 --> 00:02:56,322
- she acted like her younger self.
- Exactly.

87
00:02:56,323 --> 00:02:58,762
- I am a bit older now.
- Tae Yeon.

88
00:02:58,763 --> 00:03:00,822
- I'm an adolescent now.
- Right.

89
00:03:00,823 --> 00:03:02,232
- I'm not a little child anymore.
- You're an adolescent.

90
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:04,392
Su Yeon, you were here on Children's Day last year, right?

91
00:03:04,393 --> 00:03:05,832
- Yes, it was Children's Day.
- That's right.

92
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,563
- It's been a year.
- It's been almost a year.

93
00:03:08,233 --> 00:03:11,973
(1 year ago, she was overflowing with cuteness.)

94
00:03:15,243 --> 00:03:19,843
(Her singing skills were surprising, considering her cute appearance.)

95
00:03:20,883 --> 00:03:23,152
(This charming kid made Ho Dong put his hands together.)

96
00:03:23,153 --> 00:03:25,152
How did your friends react to your appearance on this show?

97
00:03:25,153 --> 00:03:27,452
My friends were so jealous of me being on this show...

98
00:03:27,453 --> 00:03:28,922
and meeting you all.

99
00:03:28,923 --> 00:03:31,322
They totally flipped out.

100
00:03:31,323 --> 00:03:33,522
- "They totally flipped out?"
- "They totally flipped out."

101
00:03:33,523 --> 00:03:34,692
Looking at Su Yeon's face...

102
00:03:34,693 --> 00:03:36,192
- makes me happy.
- I know, right?

103
00:03:36,193 --> 00:03:37,532
- She keeps smiling. She looks...
- Thank you.

104
00:03:37,533 --> 00:03:39,132
- like a cartoon character. Right?
- She's cute.

105
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,432
Tae Yeon,

106
00:03:40,433 --> 00:03:42,503
what's the age gap between you and Su Yeon?

107
00:03:43,203 --> 00:03:44,532
- Are we two years apart?
- Two years?

108
00:03:44,533 --> 00:03:45,542
- Yes, we're two years apart.
- It's a surprisingly small age gap.

109
00:03:45,543 --> 00:03:47,072
- You're only two years apart?
- They're not that far apart in age.

110
00:03:47,073 --> 00:03:48,472
- Tae Yeon.
- I have something to tell you.

111
00:03:48,473 --> 00:03:50,212
They're only two years apart, but Tae Yeon always tells her,

112
00:03:50,213 --> 00:03:53,042
- "Baby, you don't know anything."
- That's right.

113
00:03:53,043 --> 00:03:54,382
- She always says that.
- She really is like a baby.

114
00:03:54,383 --> 00:03:55,912
My goodness.

115
00:03:55,913 --> 00:03:58,182
- As if she were an adult.
- Tae Yeon, you made...

116
00:03:58,183 --> 00:04:00,082
- your trot debut a long time ago.
- Exactly.

117
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:02,552
- Yes, that's right.
- Has your attitude changed...

118
00:04:02,553 --> 00:04:04,893
since becoming a senior singer?

119
00:04:05,119 --> 00:04:08,318
Although my true color comes out from time to time,

120
00:04:08,393 --> 00:04:09,892
since she's younger than me,

121
00:04:09,893 --> 00:04:11,592
I should look after her.

122
00:04:11,593 --> 00:04:13,202
- I'm trying to do so.
- That's great.

123
00:04:13,203 --> 00:04:15,532
- That's so nice of her.
- Tae Yeon, you'll grow even taller.

124
00:04:15,533 --> 00:04:17,732
- Exactly.
- Yes, I think so.

125
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:19,502
- Right.
- Just like Tae Yeon,

126
00:04:19,503 --> 00:04:21,173
Su Yeon will also...

127
00:04:21,543 --> 00:04:24,172
- come back much taller...
- Right.

128
00:04:24,173 --> 00:04:25,882
- in a couple of years.
- No, that won't happen.

129
00:04:25,883 --> 00:04:26,883
People whose names start with "Lee Soo..."

130
00:04:26,883 --> 00:04:27,883
or "Lee Su" usually don't grow tall.

131
00:04:27,884 --> 00:04:29,652
- Come on.
- Just like Lee Soo Geun?

132
00:04:29,653 --> 00:04:31,482
- Why would you say such a thing?
- You... Why would you...

133
00:04:31,483 --> 00:04:32,982
- How could you...
- That's not true.

134
00:04:32,983 --> 00:04:34,322
- She shouldn't grow tall.
- Why did you say that?

135
00:04:34,323 --> 00:04:36,522
- She won't be cute once she's tall.
- What is he talking about?

136
00:04:36,523 --> 00:04:38,192
Su Yeon is only cute because she's small.

137
00:04:38,193 --> 00:04:39,193
- Why would you...
- Lee Soo...

138
00:04:39,193 --> 00:04:40,193
Su Yeon, you agree with me, right?

139
00:04:40,194 --> 00:04:42,062
- Su Yeon is devastated.
- Who?

140
00:04:42,063 --> 00:04:44,132
- Su Yeon, just cry.
- She's shocked.

141
00:04:44,133 --> 00:04:45,862
- She's shocked.
- Aren't you from the Lee family?

142
00:04:45,863 --> 00:04:46,863
(Crying)

143
00:04:46,864 --> 00:04:48,873
Su Yeon, how tall do you want to be?

144
00:04:49,103 --> 00:04:50,633
How much do you want to grow?

145
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:53,072
- I want to be 167cm tall.
- As tall as Jang Hoon?

146
00:04:53,073 --> 00:04:54,402
- I think you will.
- If that happens, you'll be...

147
00:04:54,403 --> 00:04:55,912
- much taller than Soo Geun.
- Right.

148
00:04:55,913 --> 00:04:57,912
Solji must be 167cm tall.

149
00:04:57,913 --> 00:04:59,582
- No, Solji is...
- I'm 170cm tall.

150
00:04:59,583 --> 00:05:01,343
- She's 170cm tall.
- You want to be as tall as me, yes?

151
00:05:01,913 --> 00:05:05,112
Su Yeon, would you rather stay small like you are now...

152
00:05:05,113 --> 00:05:06,483
or grow as tall as Jang Hoon?

153
00:05:06,953 --> 00:05:09,392
- Do you want to be 2m tall?
- You have to choose between those.

154
00:05:09,393 --> 00:05:10,792
- You have only two options.
- You have to choose between them.

155
00:05:10,793 --> 00:05:13,862
Why would you ask her such a cruel question? She's just a kid.

156
00:05:13,863 --> 00:05:16,392
- Be honest with us.
- That's a hard question.

157
00:05:16,393 --> 00:05:18,832
With Solji, you guys look like a new girl group.

158
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,962
- Oh, that's right. Yes.
- A six-member girl group.

159
00:05:20,963 --> 00:05:23,002
- She's our leader.
- Yes, we're a new girl group.

160
00:05:23,003 --> 00:05:24,072
(She can't hide her girl group leader vibes.)

161
00:05:24,073 --> 00:05:26,702
- Ji Yun came here a few times.
- Right.

162
00:05:26,703 --> 00:05:28,612
But she and Solji haven't been here...

163
00:05:28,613 --> 00:05:29,613
- in such a long time.
- That's right.

164
00:05:29,614 --> 00:05:31,142
- It's been a really long time.
- It's been ages.

165
00:05:31,143 --> 00:05:32,212
- I missed you all.
- Me too.

166
00:05:32,213 --> 00:05:33,642
How have you two been?

167
00:05:33,643 --> 00:05:34,913
My gosh. What's with him?

168
00:05:35,143 --> 00:05:36,352
- How have you been?
- As for me,

169
00:05:36,353 --> 00:05:39,522
I appeared on "The King of Active Trot Singers 3,"

170
00:05:39,523 --> 00:05:42,122
which was my first trot survival show.

171
00:05:42,123 --> 00:05:43,852
I also played in a musical...

172
00:05:43,853 --> 00:05:46,192
and held concerts in foreign countries as EXID.

173
00:05:46,193 --> 00:05:47,322
I've been quite busy.

174
00:05:47,323 --> 00:05:48,692
- I see.
- You've been really busy.

175
00:05:48,693 --> 00:05:50,962
- EXID is still active.
- Right.

176
00:05:50,963 --> 00:05:52,032
- That's right.
- Sing their latest song.

177
00:05:52,033 --> 00:05:53,502
In 1, 2, 3, 4.

178
00:05:53,503 --> 00:05:55,432
Up and down, up and down

179
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:56,832
- Their latest song is...
- That's their latest song?

180
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:57,833
That's right.

181
00:05:57,834 --> 00:05:59,673
- The latest song is "down" to "up."
- He made her laugh.

182
00:06:00,043 --> 00:06:02,113
- Down and up, down and up - Down and up

183
00:06:02,373 --> 00:06:03,642
Ji Yun, how have you been?

184
00:06:03,643 --> 00:06:06,312
I've been studying hard to be a good trot singer...

185
00:06:06,313 --> 00:06:08,012
- and performing at events.
- I see.

186
00:06:08,013 --> 00:06:09,412
I've been living my life to the fullest.

187
00:06:09,413 --> 00:06:12,283
As for Su Kyung and Hye Yeon, this is their first time...

188
00:06:12,553 --> 00:06:14,352
- on Men on a Mission.
- That's right.

189
00:06:14,353 --> 00:06:16,992
I had never been on TV before "The King of Active Trot Singers 3."

190
00:06:16,993 --> 00:06:19,522
- Since I was an unknown singer...
- She didn't have a chance.

191
00:06:19,523 --> 00:06:21,522
- Exactly. I didn't have a chance.
- Right.

192
00:06:21,523 --> 00:06:23,193
Why didn't you just come?

193
00:06:23,763 --> 00:06:25,862
- I wasn't invited.
- You could just drop by.

194
00:06:25,863 --> 00:06:27,332
Why didn't you come out when we introduced our guests?

195
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,672
- She wasn't invited.
- Exactly. I should've done that.

196
00:06:28,673 --> 00:06:31,502
- Like they do after the opening.
- Exactly.

197
00:06:31,503 --> 00:06:34,603
- I wish she had done that.
- Is this your first time seeing us?

198
00:06:35,043 --> 00:06:36,142
That's right. I've only seen you on TV.

199
00:06:36,143 --> 00:06:37,742
I still feel like I'm watching TV.

200
00:06:37,743 --> 00:06:39,082
- Have you not met any of us?
- No.

201
00:06:39,083 --> 00:06:40,643
Have you not seen any of us, even on the street?

202
00:06:41,043 --> 00:06:42,612
- No. Only on TV...
- Not even Yeong Cheol?

203
00:06:42,613 --> 00:06:44,352
- That's right.
- Then she's never seen any of us.

204
00:06:44,353 --> 00:06:46,222
- Now that you've met us, - It's her first time seeing us.

205
00:06:46,223 --> 00:06:47,652
tell us about your first impressions of us.

206
00:06:47,653 --> 00:06:50,123
To be honest, Ho Dong seems...

207
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:51,752
thinner in person than I imagined.

208
00:06:51,753 --> 00:06:53,092
Well... That's right.

209
00:06:53,093 --> 00:06:55,223
- You look way thinner...
- How did you picture me?

210
00:06:55,593 --> 00:06:57,632
I mean, on TV, you look very broad...

211
00:06:57,633 --> 00:06:58,633
- People look broader on screen.
- I mean...

212
00:06:58,634 --> 00:07:00,732
- How do I look on screen?
- You mean, sturdier than in person?

213
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,872
He looks sturdier on screen than he looks in person.

214
00:07:02,873 --> 00:07:04,132
He seems strong and healthy when you look at his legs and all.

215
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:05,133
- Exactly.
- He has strong legs.

216
00:07:05,134 --> 00:07:06,942
You looked thinner than I expected, which surprised me.

217
00:07:06,943 --> 00:07:08,472
You were surprised because I was thinner than expected?

218
00:07:08,473 --> 00:07:10,942
Soo Geun seems smaller than I imagined.

219
00:07:10,943 --> 00:07:12,542
- Right?
- You seem smaller than I thought.

220
00:07:12,543 --> 00:07:14,512
- It's because I'm behind Ho Dong.
- He looks cute.

221
00:07:14,513 --> 00:07:16,612
Jang Hoon looks taller than I expected.

222
00:07:16,613 --> 00:07:17,983
So, briefly speaking,

223
00:07:18,283 --> 00:07:21,252
- we look broad, small, and tall.
- He's very tall.

224
00:07:21,253 --> 00:07:23,822
- That's all that caught her eye.
- That's right.

225
00:07:23,823 --> 00:07:26,062
- Broad, small, and tall.
- Tall.

226
00:07:26,063 --> 00:07:27,592
(To her, they're simply the tall, the broad, and the small.)

227
00:07:27,593 --> 00:07:30,062
- The beanpole, fatty, and shorty.
- What about you, Hye Yeon?

228
00:07:30,063 --> 00:07:32,702
I really wanted to meet Hee Chul...

229
00:07:32,703 --> 00:07:34,662
because when I was active as a member of BESTie,

230
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:36,672
Hee Chul interviewed me for a show.

231
00:07:36,673 --> 00:07:37,972
That's right. I was a big fan.

232
00:07:37,973 --> 00:07:40,142
He told us a lot of heartwarming things.

233
00:07:40,143 --> 00:07:41,302
- What did he tell you?
- What kind of things?

234
00:07:41,303 --> 00:07:43,412
- Hee Chul said heartwarming things?
- Yes.

