00:15:45,453 --> 00:15:48,122
My classmates helped me a lot, giving me a lot of advice.

471
00:15:48,123 --> 00:15:49,592
So I've been doing well at school.

472
00:15:49,593 --> 00:15:52,432
- Don't you miss your friends...
- Right.

473
00:15:52,433 --> 00:15:54,002
in Gyeongju?

474
00:15:54,003 --> 00:15:55,762
- Do you keep in touch with them?
- Of course, she misses them.

475
00:15:55,763 --> 00:15:58,673
I do miss my friends in Gyeongju,

476
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:00,903
but we're all busy living our lives.

477
00:16:01,703 --> 00:16:03,073
My friends are busy.

478
00:16:03,143 --> 00:16:04,672
- And I'm busy too.
- I guess she doesn't look back...

479
00:16:04,673 --> 00:16:06,213
once she decides to end relationships.

480
00:16:06,583 --> 00:16:08,313
How could you say such a thing about a little child?

481
00:16:08,413 --> 00:16:10,883
- It's because she's busy.
- Why do you keep getting at her?

482
00:16:11,083 --> 00:16:12,312
Su Yeon, I heard you were going to sing for us.

483
00:16:12,313 --> 00:16:13,322
- Yes, I will.
- Really?

484
00:16:13,323 --> 00:16:16,252
I'm going to sing "You So Far Away."

485
00:16:16,253 --> 00:16:17,722
- That's random.
- That's such a sad song.

486
00:16:17,723 --> 00:16:20,393
- She'll suddenly sing a sad song.
- They really are far away from her.

487
00:16:20,563 --> 00:16:22,733
- The song makes me want to cry.
- It's a gift for her old friends.

488
00:16:22,793 --> 00:16:26,132
- It's about longing for someone.
- Her old friends are in Gyeongju.

489
00:16:26,133 --> 00:16:28,032
- How will she sing that song?
- This song requires...

490
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:30,773
- a lot of life experience.
- A round of applause.

491
00:16:31,503 --> 00:16:32,672
- Play the song.
- Go, Su Yeon!

492
00:16:32,673 --> 00:16:33,773
The golden youngest member!

493
00:16:34,903 --> 00:16:39,213
(She switches off her smile to immerse herself in the song.)

494
00:16:39,913 --> 00:16:42,952
("You So Far Away" performed by Lee Su Yeon, )

495
00:16:42,953 --> 00:16:44,953
(original song by Kim Choo Ja)

496
00:18:28,253 --> 00:18:32,252
(While I was hesitating)

497
00:18:32,253 --> 00:18:36,563
(While I was hesitating)

498
00:18:40,003 --> 00:18:45,332
(You)

499
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:48,403
(Went so far away)

500
00:18:48,773 --> 00:18:54,013
(Su Yeon's sincerity must've reached her friends in Gyeongju.)

501
00:18:55,083 --> 00:18:56,282
- Great job, Su Yeon.
- That was amazing.

502
00:18:56,283 --> 00:18:58,552
- Her friends will be crying.
- She's our pride.

503
00:18:58,553 --> 00:19:01,123
Su Yeon, you're really...

504
00:19:01,883 --> 00:19:03,692
My goodness. That was insane.

505
00:19:03,693 --> 00:19:05,553
I think I should...

506
00:19:05,823 --> 00:19:08,492
- get her autograph now.
- How does she do that?

507
00:19:08,493 --> 00:19:10,362
- She's incredible.
- She's our pride.

508
00:19:10,363 --> 00:19:11,692
She's amazing.

509
00:19:11,693 --> 00:19:13,733
Following their nicknames,

510
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:15,632
our guests wrote...

511
00:19:15,633 --> 00:19:18,932
about the stories behind "The King of Active Trot Singers 3."

512
00:19:18,933 --> 00:19:20,942
The keyword of the first story is "Winning."

513
00:19:20,943 --> 00:19:22,442
(Stories behind "The King of Active Trot Singers 3," Winning)

514
00:19:22,443 --> 00:19:23,843
Based on the keyword, it must be Ji Yun's story.

515
00:19:24,013 --> 00:19:25,213
- Yes. I won the competition.
- Right?

516
00:19:26,443 --> 00:19:28,542
(Hong Ji Yun, winner of "The King of Active Trot Singers 3")

517
00:19:28,543 --> 00:19:29,883
As expected!

518
00:19:30,813 --> 00:19:32,412
What about in "Miss Trot 2?"

519
00:19:32,413 --> 00:19:33,952
- I came in second.
- The runner-up?

520
00:19:33,953 --> 00:19:34,953
Yes, the runner-up.

521
00:19:35,123 --> 00:19:37,252
- You came in second back then, - Correct.

522
00:19:37,253 --> 00:19:38,592
- but won this time.
- Yes.

523
00:19:38,593 --> 00:19:40,422
Wasn't "The King of Active Trot Singers" more competitive?

524
00:19:40,423 --> 00:19:41,692
- Absolutely.
- Right?

525
00:19:41,693 --> 00:19:44,133
- I could tell.
- She was sick of coming in second.

526
00:19:44,893 --> 00:19:47,503
That's why she tried again. Right, Ji Yun?

527
00:19:47,563 --> 00:19:49,332
More than that...

528
00:19:49,333 --> 00:19:50,772
Of course, that's one of the reasons.

529
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:52,433
Wherever I went,

530
00:19:52,503 --> 00:19:54,972
people were like, "You came in second back then."

531
00:19:54,973 --> 00:19:56,742
- I heard that nonstop.
- Right.

532
00:19:56,743 --> 00:19:58,972
"I thought you'd come in 1st, but you came in 2nd."

533
00:19:58,973 --> 00:20:02,182
"I felt bad." People kept saying that.

534
00:20:02,183 --> 00:20:03,452
I competed...

535
00:20:03,453 --> 00:20:06,582
without much preparation back then.

536
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:09,253
And working as a singer soon after that...

537
00:20:09,383 --> 00:20:11,352
made me realize the improvements I could make.

538
00:20:11,353 --> 00:20:13,892
With that, I thought to myself...

539
00:20:13,893 --> 00:20:16,092
that I needed time to work on my skills more,

540
00:20:16,093 --> 00:20:18,863
so I studied trot a lot more.

541
00:20:18,993 --> 00:20:21,302
Here came the chance to compete in "The King of Active Trot Singers 3."

542
00:20:21,303 --> 00:20:25,072
I wanted to put what I studied to good use,

543
00:20:25,073 --> 00:20:26,102
- so I took part...
- You won.

544
00:20:26,103 --> 00:20:27,103
and got a good result.

545
00:20:27,104 --> 00:20:29,742
What is it like? Is coming in first different, as expected?

546
00:20:29,743 --> 00:20:33,912
The staff who work with me were happier than I was.

547
00:20:33,913 --> 00:20:35,912
They're excited to work with a first-place singer.

548
00:20:35,913 --> 00:20:37,712
That's what makes me happy.

549
00:20:37,713 --> 00:20:39,283
- Right.
- What matters is...

550
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:41,982
Weren't there participants who gave off...

551
00:20:41,983 --> 00:20:43,852
- Yes.
- a different vibe?

552
00:20:43,853 --> 00:20:45,952
- I studied everyone like this.
- Right.

553
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:47,362
"What is she wearing?"

554
00:20:47,363 --> 00:20:49,323
"To think she'd take part in it."

555
00:20:49,563 --> 00:20:50,892
I studied everyone thoroughly.

556
00:20:50,893 --> 00:20:53,633
But who shocked me the most was Cha Ji Yeon.

557
00:20:54,303 --> 00:20:57,403
The minute her name, Cha Ji Yeon, popped up on the screen,

558
00:20:57,573 --> 00:20:58,833
I got goosebumps...

559
00:20:59,073 --> 00:21:01,372
and wasn't sure if trying again...

560
00:21:01,373 --> 00:21:02,502
- was the right choice.
- I see.

561
00:21:02,503 --> 00:21:04,512
- "Spring Is Gone."
- Yes.

562
00:21:04,513 --> 00:21:06,212
- I cried.
- Same here.

563
00:21:06,213 --> 00:21:07,883
- I cried my eyes out.
- I see.

564
00:21:08,583 --> 00:21:10,052
- She came in second.
- Yes.

565
00:21:10,053 --> 00:21:11,452
- She did.
- Right?

566
00:21:11,453 --> 00:21:13,453
Is she sulking after coming in second? Is that why she's not here?

567
00:21:13,823 --> 00:21:16,153
- Yes, you're right.
- Yes.

568
00:21:16,523 --> 00:21:17,552
- Right?
- No, they're lying.

569
00:21:17,553 --> 00:21:19,123
Tae Yeon is back.

570
00:21:20,193 --> 00:21:21,222
Is she not here because she's sulking?

571
00:21:21,223 --> 00:21:24,062
No, she has a musical rehearsal to attend.

572
00:21:24,063 --> 00:21:25,892
- No, she's definitely sulking.
- Is she?

573
00:21:25,893 --> 00:21:27,002
No.

574
00:21:27,003 --> 00:21:28,502
- Let's be honest, Solji.
- Okay.

575
00:21:28,503 --> 00:21:30,572
Who was your biggest competition?

576
00:21:30,573 --> 00:21:32,460
I didn't really know...

577
00:21:32,786 --> 00:21:35,686
the singers in the trot industry.

578
00:21:35,773 --> 00:21:39,372
Remember how we listened to everyone sing during the preliminary round?

579
00:21:39,373 --> 00:21:43,652
There was one singer who I thought, "Compete against here,"

580
00:21:43,653 --> 00:21:45,313
- "and I'd be dead meat."
- Who was it?

581
00:21:45,453 --> 00:21:46,982
- Su Yeon.
- Yes.

582
00:21:46,983 --> 00:21:48,253
- She's a kid.
- Right.

583
00:21:48,353 --> 00:21:50,252
And see how she's smiling brightly?

584
00:21:50,253 --> 00:21:51,822
I thought she'd be baby-like.

585
00:21:51,823 --> 00:21:53,922
She was also the youngest among us.

586
00:21:53,923 --> 00:21:55,593
But the minute she started singing,

587
00:21:55,693 --> 00:21:57,263
- she became a different person.
- True.

588
00:21:57,793 --> 00:21:59,732
A child's emotions can't be imitated...

589
00:21:59,733 --> 00:22:01,662
- by adults.
- No.

590
00:22:01,663 --> 00:22:04,932
I couldn't possibly compete against her.

591
00:22:04,933 --> 00:22:06,242
- I get it.
- Even in comic books,

592
00:22:06,243 --> 00:22:07,243
those who smile brightly...

593
00:22:07,244 --> 00:22:08,642
- are the strongest.
- Right?

594
00:22:08,643 --> 00:22:09,912
- For real.
- I'm a comic book addict.

595
00:22:09,913 --> 00:22:10,972
Cheerful characters are the strongest.

596
00:22:10,973 --> 00:22:12,882
Even in "Demon Slayer," the smiling ones are the scariest.

597
00:22:12,883 --> 00:22:14,482
- Exactly.
- Right?

598
00:22:14,483 --> 00:22:15,483
Those who are smiling...

599
00:22:15,483 --> 00:22:16,483
- are the scariest.
- Exactly.

600
00:22:16,484 --> 00:22:18,412
Ji Yun, what did you think after listening to Solji sing?

601
00:22:18,413 --> 00:22:20,552
First and foremost, Solji has no ups and downs.

602
00:22:20,553 --> 00:22:22,892
- She's got a good foundation.
- I agree.

603
00:22:22,893 --> 00:22:25,222
- Solji is always good.
- Solji is a great singer.

604
00:22:25,223 --> 00:22:26,223
What's more, she's the first king on...

605
00:22:26,223 --> 00:22:27,223
"The King of Mask Singer."

606
00:22:27,263 --> 00:22:28,263
- The best.
- The king.

607
00:22:28,264 --> 00:22:30,662
Solji, the trot industry is...

608
00:22:30,663 --> 00:22:32,332
- no joke, right?
- No.

609
00:22:32,333 --> 00:22:34,062
- Trot is...
- It wasn't easy.

610
00:22:34,063 --> 00:22:36,572
Sang Min is asking like a trot producer.

611
00:22:36,573 --> 00:22:37,732
He asked as if...

612
00:22:37,733 --> 00:22:40,342
- No joke, right?
- he were a great master of trot.

613
00:22:40,343 --> 00:22:43,312
- "It was no joke, right?"
- "No joke."

614
00:22:43,313 --> 00:22:46,142
He's giving off trot producer vibes.

615
00:22:46,143 --> 00:22:47,412
- Totally.
- Right?

616
00:22:47,413 --> 00:22:48,682
- What's more...
- But you did it.

617
00:22:48,683 --> 00:22:49,812
What about saying "the genre trot..."

618
00:22:49,813 --> 00:22:51,882
- and not "trot industry?"
- Exactly.

619
00:22:51,883 --> 00:22:54,823
But producers usually say "industry."

620
00:22:56,023 --> 00:22:57,852
- That's how we talk.
- He's going to lose money again.

621
00:22:57,853 --> 00:23:00,262
- Is it a producer's language?
- Yes, language.

622
00:23:00,263 --> 00:23:02,562
Solji, what did you find the toughest?

623
00:23:02,563 --> 00:23:05,262
I wanted to have fun being on the show,

624
00:23:05,263 --> 00:23:06,932
and I did my best when performing.

625
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:08,302
I tried to have as much fun as possible.

626
00:23:08,303 --> 00:23:10,202
But people said I was smiling too much.

627
00:23:10,203 --> 00:23:11,872
- Smiling?
- When it's a contest show?

628
00:23:11,873 --> 00:23:14,272
Yes, I was smiling too much and looked too cheerful.

629
00:23:14,273 --> 00:23:15,402
Were you criticized for having fun?

630
00:23:15,403 --> 00:23:17,942
Yes, people were expecting me to be all stressed out...

631
00:23:17,943 --> 00:23:21,082
and to want to come in first place no matter what.

632
00:23:21,083 --> 00:23:24,783
Honestly, it's something I heard quite often.

633
00:23:25,483 --> 00:23:27,082
- I found...
- As it is a kind of competition,

634
00:23:27,083 --> 00:23:30,292
I'm sure some songs were just right up Su Kyung's alley.

635
00:23:30,293 --> 00:23:32,392
Was there a time your favorite song...

636
00:23:32,393 --> 00:23:34,123
overlapped with someone else's?

637
00:23:34,323 --> 00:23:35,792
No, there wasn't.

638
00:23:35,793 --> 00:23:37,262
But I started off singing...

639
00:23:37,263 --> 00:23:40,332
- rock ballads.
- You did rock.

640
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:44,873
So I was a big fan of Kyung Hoon, who is over there.

641
00:23:44,973 --> 00:23:47,303
- He was in a band.
- What songs did you like?

642
00:23:48,243 --> 00:23:49,442
I liked "Thorn."

643
00:23:49,443 --> 00:23:51,143
- You are going to mimic him, right?
- In 1, 2, 3, 4.

644
00:23:51,673 --> 00:23:53,382
(Singing)

645
00:23:53,383 --> 00:23:54,543
Why...

646
00:23:54,843 --> 00:23:56,512
(Singing)

647
00:23:56,513 --> 00:23:58,012
(Ridiculing Min Kyung Hoon)

648
00:23:58,013 --> 00:24:00,122
- Hold on.
- That's just my version.

649
00:24:00,123 --> 00:24:02,582
- Why did you imitate Kim Hee Chul?
- Why are you...

650
00:24:02,583 --> 00:24:04,753
That was something Hee Chul made up.

651
00:24:04,893 --> 00:24:06,192
- Wait.
- Su Kyung.

652
00:24:06,193 --> 00:24:08,622
I'd better make it on the show, right?

653
00:24:08,623 --> 00:24:10,432
You're good. Su Kyung, you're good.

654
00:24:10,433 --> 00:24:11,762
- She came prepared.
- I practiced.

655
00:24:11,763 --> 00:24:13,232
- I did all night long.
- Is that so?

656
00:24:13,233 --> 00:24:15,662
- Try again.
- You could've sung normally.

657
00:24:15,663 --> 00:24:17,333
- There was no need for this.
- Right.

658
00:24:17,603 --> 00:24:20,142
- Why attack him out of nowhere?
- She reminded me of my dad.

659
00:24:20,143 --> 00:24:21,272
She came prepared.

660
00:24:21,273 --> 00:24:22,672
- She did.
- Try again.

661
00:24:22,673 --> 00:24:23,913
Then...

662
00:24:23,973 --> 00:24:25,242
- There's more later.
- Lee Yong Jin.

663
00:24:25,243 --> 00:24:26,782
- Do Lee Yong Jin.
- Right now?

664
00:24:26,783 --> 00:24:28,582
- It's the perfect time.
- Yes.

665
00:24:28,583 --> 00:24:30,653
- Lee Yong Jin, whom we know?
- Then...

666
00:24:30,813 --> 00:24:32,312
- The comedian?
- Yes, Seup Teun Hoon.

667
00:24:32,313 --> 00:24:33,682
- Yes, Jang Hoon.
- Yes.

668
00:24:33,683 --> 00:24:36,052
This is comedian Lee Yong Jin imitating...

669
00:24:36,053 --> 00:24:37,952
- Kim Jang Hoon.
- Okay.

670
00:24:37,953 --> 00:24:39,492
- Interesting.
- Nice.

671
00:24:39,493 --> 00:24:41,093
- Good. Show them.
- Let's go.

672
00:24:42,093 --> 00:24:45,263
(Singing)

673
00:24:45,393 --> 00:24:47,002
(I miss you so much)

674
00:24:47,003 --> 00:24:48,563
(Crying)

675
00:24:50,733 --> 00:24:53,343
That's simply ridiculing him.

676
00:24:53,543 --> 00:24:55,202
That's how Yong Jin does it.

677
00:24:55,203 --> 00:24:56,972
That's just ridiculing him.

678
00:24:56,973 --> 00:24:58,472
- Next.
- Since I'm already at it,

679
00:24:58,473 --> 00:24:59,473
- should I do more?
- Show us everything.

680
00:24:59,474 --> 00:25:03,212
I'll move on to comedians.

681
00:25:03,213 --> 00:25:04,352
Park Myung Soo.

682
00:25:04,353 --> 00:25:05,852
- Myung Soo?
- Even Myung Soo?

683
00:25:05,853 --> 00:25:07,023
Let's go.

684
00:25:07,853 --> 00:25:08,922
- What?
- That was bad, right?

685
00:25:08,923 --> 00:25:09,952
Here's Jung Jun Ha.

686
00:25:09,953 --> 00:25:11,552
- Move on quickly.
- Jung Jun Ha.

687
00:25:11,553 --> 00:25:13,592
I'll keep the momentum going and try Jung Jun Ha.

688
00:25:13,593 --> 00:25:14,623
She's trying hard.

689
00:25:15,793 --> 00:25:18,163
I'm going to dig in for sure.

690
00:25:18,363 --> 00:25:20,902
Her specialties are like a cheap department store.

691
00:25:20,903 --> 00:25:23,502
There's simply a collection of them.

692
00:25:23,503 --> 00:25:26,132
(Min Kyung Hoon)

693
00:25:26,133 --> 00:25:28,272
(I came prepared with all sorts.)

694
00:25:28,273 --> 00:25:29,402
(Park Myung Soo)

695
00:25:29,403 --> 00:25:31,243
(Jung Jun Ha)

696
00:25:31,543 --> 00:25:35,343
Tae Yeon, you're still in your teens.

697
00:25:35,483 --> 00:25:37,012
Aren't there many lyrics you don't understand?

698
00:25:37,013 --> 00:25:38,753
There's a ton.

699
00:25:39,053 --> 00:25:40,722
In "The King of Active Trot Singers 3,"

700
00:25:40,723 --> 00:25:42,953
- for example, I sang "Repentance."
- I remember.

701
00:25:43,223 --> 00:25:44,752
("Repentance" by Choi Jin Hee)

702
00:25:44,753 --> 00:25:48,093
(A traditional trot about regretting and missing her past love)

703
00:25:48,363 --> 00:25:50,632
I didn't even know what repentance meant.

704
00:25:50,633 --> 00:25:53,533
Say it incorrectly, and it'd be the fruit with the same pronunciation.

705
00:25:54,163 --> 00:25:56,262
- That's why...
- Cute.

706
00:25:56,263 --> 00:25:59,072
I wondered if it was the old word for oriental melon...

707
00:25:59,073 --> 00:26:00,542
- Repentance.
- and did some research.

708
00:26:00,543 --> 00:26:01,902
In a way, she's a genius.

709
00:26:01,903 --> 00:26:03,472
- Totally.
- Expressing those feelings...

710
00:26:03,473 --> 00:26:04,473
despite not knowing the definition...

711
00:26:04,473 --> 00:26:05,473
- For sure.
- is amazing.

712
00:26:05,474 --> 00:26:08,642
Most of trot is about love.

713
00:26:08,643 --> 00:26:10,753
- Either about love or breakups.
- Right.

714
00:26:10,883 --> 00:26:13,222
But I've never been in love...

715
00:26:13,223 --> 00:26:15,322
- or experienced a breakup.
-True.

716
00:26:15,323 --> 00:26:18,022
When I'm lost, I ask my grandma,

717
00:26:18,023 --> 00:26:21,893
"This song is about love. How should I express the feelings?"

718
00:26:22,093 --> 00:26:25,792
For example, "Try singing it while thinking of..."

719
00:26:25,793 --> 00:26:28,962
"family love." That's the kind of answer she gives me.

720
00:26:28,963 --> 00:26:31,372
I sang songs by understanding the lyrics like that.

721
00:26:31,373 --> 00:26:32,772
- Same here.
- Really.

722
00:26:32,773 --> 00:26:35,142
She's much better at interviews than any adults.

723
00:26:35,143 --> 00:26:36,542
- For sure.
- Right?

724
00:26:36,543 --> 00:26:38,643
- She's the smartest.
- I'm serious.

725
00:26:38,943 --> 00:26:40,442
- Really, she puts me in awe...
- Yes.

726
00:26:40,443 --> 00:26:41,942
- every single time.
- Seriously.

727
00:26:41,943 --> 00:26:44,182
- She's good.
- Model answers.

728
00:26:44,183 --> 00:26:46,413
She answers with model answers...

729
00:26:46,783 --> 00:26:48,352
- with zero mistakes.
- True.

730
00:26:48,353 --> 00:26:50,552
Do an interview with all seven of us,

731
00:26:50,553 --> 00:26:52,022
- and you'd be in 1st or 2nd place.
- For sure.

732
00:26:52,023 --> 00:26:53,793
- It'll be you and Seo Jang Hoon.
- No way.

733
00:26:53,963 --> 00:26:56,122
By the way, I heard...

734
00:26:56,123 --> 00:26:58,262
it was tough for Ji Yun to sing on stage...

735
00:26:58,263 --> 00:26:59,362
- for a while.
- That's right.

736
00:26:59,363 --> 00:27:01,732
As you know, I became a singer through an audition.

737
00:27:01,733 --> 00:27:04,002
I started being loved out of nowhere,

738
00:27:04,003 --> 00:27:06,803
and many became fans of me,

739
00:27:06,903 --> 00:27:10,773
but just as many people started hating me.

740
00:27:11,113 --> 00:27:13,073
I was having a meal at a restaurant...

741
00:27:13,243 --> 00:27:14,843
when a customer behind recognized me...

742
00:27:15,143 --> 00:27:16,752
and badmouthed me.

743
00:27:16,753 --> 00:27:18,882
- What a bad person.
- You heard that?

744
00:27:18,883 --> 00:27:22,122
I did. It came as a great shock to me.

745
00:27:22,123 --> 00:27:24,053
Since then, I kept wondering,

746
00:27:24,093 --> 00:27:26,322
"What do they think about me? After hearing my song..."

747
00:27:26,323 --> 00:27:27,992
- whenever I got on stage.
- It's a sort of panic attack.

748
00:27:27,993 --> 00:27:29,462
- It's become traumatic.
- Yes.

749
00:27:29,463 --> 00:27:31,033
I went through such a period.

750
00:27:31,263 --> 00:27:35,032
I overcame it by thinking...

751
00:27:35,033 --> 00:27:37,232
there are still many who love me.

752
00:27:37,233 --> 00:27:39,672
To overcome it, take a look at Seo Jang Hoon.

753
00:27:39,673 --> 00:27:41,072
When he was a pro athlete...

754
00:27:41,073 --> 00:27:42,402
We were cursed,

755
00:27:42,403 --> 00:27:44,842
hit by coins when leaving,

756
00:27:44,843 --> 00:27:46,342
- and such.
- Even coins?

757
00:27:46,343 --> 00:27:48,713
He collected all those coins and became rich.

758
00:27:48,913 --> 00:27:51,752
It's because he endured and overcame it.

759
00:27:51,753 --> 00:27:53,653
With that, he bought buildings.

760
00:27:53,783 --> 00:27:55,222
He has assets worth two billion.

761
00:27:55,223 --> 00:27:56,723
- I see.
- That's what happened.

762
00:27:57,293 --> 00:28:00,022
You're given countless missions, right?

763
00:28:00,023 --> 00:28:01,522
- Yes.
- Either way, you all competed...

764
00:28:01,523 --> 00:28:03,932
- and ranked in the top seven.
- Exactly.

765
00:28:03,933 --> 00:28:05,933
Will you be on shows together from now on?

766
00:28:06,193 --> 00:28:09,363
- Yes.
- Right. Starting March 28,

767
00:28:09,463 --> 00:28:13,242
we'll be on a national concert tour starting in Seoul.

768
00:28:13,243 --> 00:28:15,302
Together with it,

769
00:28:15,303 --> 00:28:18,113
we'll be on "Korea-Japan King of Singers" starting April.

770
00:28:18,273 --> 00:28:19,612
It's between the top seven of Korea...

771
00:28:19,613 --> 00:28:21,312
- and the top seven of Japan.
- It's a fun show.

772
00:28:21,313 --> 00:28:23,453
The real deal starts in that show.

773
00:28:24,183 --> 00:28:27,122
- That's how we'll compete.
- It's entertaining.

774
00:28:27,123 --> 00:28:29,783
- All right.
- Let's hear a song, Solji.

775
00:28:29,923 --> 00:28:31,092
- What song?
- Your song.

776
00:28:31,093 --> 00:28:32,523
Did you not prepare one? Shall I sing instead?

777
00:28:33,463 --> 00:28:34,822
- Right, go ahead.
- No.

778
00:28:34,823 --> 00:28:35,962
- I want to hear her sing.
- I'll do it.

779
00:28:35,963 --> 00:28:38,462
Of course, Solji was in EXID.

780
00:28:38,463 --> 00:28:40,402
- Where is she?
- But now, she's a trot singer.

781
00:28:40,403 --> 00:28:41,662
- Solji.
- Let's welcome her...

782
00:28:41,663 --> 00:28:43,032
- Where did she go?
- with a big round of applause.

783
00:28:43,033 --> 00:28:45,232
- Solji!
- Where is she?

784
00:28:45,233 --> 00:28:47,173
- She needs to sing.
- Will she appear from above?

785
00:28:49,303 --> 00:28:50,612
- What?
- Hi!

786
00:28:50,613 --> 00:28:53,643
I'm SWA, a rookie trot singer!

787
00:28:54,183 --> 00:28:57,113
Nice to meet you.

788
00:28:58,183 --> 00:29:00,953
("An Odious Man" performed by Solji, original song by Yu Ji Na)

789
00:29:15,803 --> 00:29:16,933
She's skillful.

790
00:30:21,203 --> 00:30:24,432
(Odious)

791
00:30:24,433 --> 00:30:29,073
(Man)

792
00:30:31,713 --> 00:30:33,212
Thank you!

793
00:30:33,213 --> 00:30:34,582
She's good.

794
00:30:34,583 --> 00:30:35,943
She's bright.

795
00:30:36,143 --> 00:30:37,312
Her voice is like honey.

796
00:30:37,313 --> 00:30:39,353
Solji is really...

797
00:30:39,683 --> 00:30:40,882
a computer singer.

798
00:30:40,883 --> 00:30:42,352
- That's right.
- She's never gone...

799
00:30:42,353 --> 00:30:43,353
That's right.

800
00:30:43,693 --> 00:30:45,522
- flat or sharp...
- It didn't waver.

801
00:30:45,523 --> 00:30:46,552
on a single note.

802
00:30:46,553 --> 00:30:48,592
- She never...
- How much do you even know...

803
00:30:48,593 --> 00:30:49,722
about singing that you...

804
00:30:49,723 --> 00:30:50,932
He's the Deity of Music.

805
00:30:50,933 --> 00:30:51,933
Do you know trot music?

806
00:30:51,934 --> 00:30:53,032
- Thank you, Sang Min.
- He's the Deity of Music.

807
00:30:53,033 --> 00:30:54,903
Anyway, Solji is a computer singer.

808
00:30:55,303 --> 00:30:56,832
Behind the scenes of "The King of Active Trot Singers 3."

809
00:30:56,833 --> 00:30:59,603
The second one after "winning..."

810
00:30:59,903 --> 00:31:01,602
is "challenge."

811
00:31:01,603 --> 00:31:02,672
- Challenge.
- Solji mentioned that.

812
00:31:02,673 --> 00:31:05,342
I heard there is someone who is addicted to auditions...

813
00:31:05,343 --> 00:31:07,312
and is currently receiving treatment.

814
00:31:07,313 --> 00:31:09,012
- How did you get addicted to that?
- Is it Hye Yeon?

815
00:31:09,013 --> 00:31:10,013
That's me.

816
00:31:10,983 --> 00:31:13,012
After I became a singer,

817
00:31:13,013 --> 00:31:15,382
I went on audition shows five times.

818
00:31:15,383 --> 00:31:16,383
Really?

819
00:31:16,384 --> 00:31:19,222
I went on trot audition shows four times...

820
00:31:19,223 --> 00:31:21,392
and on an idol audition show once.

821
00:31:21,393 --> 00:31:22,722
Which shows were they?

822
00:31:22,723 --> 00:31:24,092
I appeared on "Trot X,"

823
00:31:24,093 --> 00:31:26,563
"The Unit" on KBS,

824
00:31:27,063 --> 00:31:30,032
"Miss Trot 2," "The King of Active Trot Singers 1,"

825
00:31:30,033 --> 00:31:33,102
and "The King of Active Trot Singers 3."

826
00:31:33,103 --> 00:31:34,242
It's actually exhausting.

827
00:31:34,243 --> 00:31:36,473
- It's very exhausting.
- I get exhausted when it's over,

828
00:31:36,873 --> 00:31:38,572
- but after some time, I feel fine.
- Right.

829
00:31:38,573 --> 00:31:39,742
I get bored.

830
00:31:39,743 --> 00:31:42,182
- Your memory gets distorted.
- I feel like...

831
00:31:42,183 --> 00:31:43,782
I need my heart to race again.

832
00:31:43,783 --> 00:31:45,852
- I get that feeling.
- That's your source of dopamine.

833
00:31:45,853 --> 00:31:46,853
It gives me dopamine.

834
00:31:46,854 --> 00:31:49,322
That's also possible because you're talented.

835
00:31:49,323 --> 00:31:50,852
Look, Hye Yeon.

836
00:31:50,853 --> 00:31:52,593
We also used to play sports.

837
00:31:52,893 --> 00:31:55,362
If you go and get eliminated in the preliminaries,

838
00:31:55,363 --> 00:31:56,722
it's easy to give up.

839
00:31:56,723 --> 00:31:58,062
- You don't even have any regrets.
- That's right.

840
00:31:58,063 --> 00:32:00,092
But you know when it feels like it's about to work out,

841
00:32:00,093 --> 00:32:01,102
- but it doesn't?
- That's right.

842
00:32:01,103 --> 00:32:02,532
- You feel frustrated.
- That's right.

843
00:32:02,533 --> 00:32:04,232
You can't give up then.

844
00:32:04,233 --> 00:32:05,972
- That's right.
- But once you fall,

845
00:32:05,973 --> 00:32:07,872
it's not easy to get back up.

846
00:32:07,873 --> 00:32:09,372
- That's right.
- I'm sorry,

847
00:32:09,373 --> 00:32:11,442
but have you ever been eliminated in the preliminaries?

848
00:32:11,443 --> 00:32:14,712
- You were totally...
- You were...

849
00:32:14,713 --> 00:32:17,312
- You always won.
- You were seriously...

850
00:32:17,313 --> 00:32:18,912
Have you ever experienced failure in your life?

851
00:32:18,913 --> 00:32:20,923
- You never did.
- Well,

852
00:32:21,123 --> 00:32:22,753
it's only the title of Chunha ssireum champion that sticks.

853
00:32:22,983 --> 00:32:25,552
I've been eliminated in the preliminaries many times.

854
00:32:25,553 --> 00:32:28,292
On shows that pick the top seven,

855
00:32:28,293 --> 00:32:30,292
like "Miss Trot 2" and "The King of Active Trot Singers 1,"

856
00:32:30,293 --> 00:32:31,293
I kept placing eighth.

857
00:32:31,793 --> 00:32:33,832
So being in the eighth place...

858
00:32:33,833 --> 00:32:34,902
That's your fate.

859
00:32:34,903 --> 00:32:36,302
My fate got twisted.

860
00:32:36,303 --> 00:32:37,303
It was so frustrating.

861
00:32:37,304 --> 00:32:39,372
I wanted to break out of that eighth place.

862
00:32:39,373 --> 00:32:40,972
- Also...
- What place did you get this time?

863
00:32:40,973 --> 00:32:42,872
- I was fifth this time.
- Goodness.

864
00:32:42,873 --> 00:32:45,012
You finally broke out of the eighth place.

865
00:32:45,013 --> 00:32:46,612
You're on an upward trend.

866
00:32:46,613 --> 00:32:47,942
- I'm on an upward trend.
- That's right.

867
00:32:47,943 --> 00:32:50,012
I was sick of number eight.

868
00:32:50,013 --> 00:32:51,952
My birthday is on December 8 as well.

869
00:32:51,953 --> 00:32:53,652
(Date of birth: December 8, 1990)

870
00:32:53,653 --> 00:32:56,152
- Goodness.
- And my first car's number plate...

871
00:32:56,153 --> 00:32:58,322
- had 1988.
- You have a lot of 8 in your fate.

872
00:32:58,323 --> 00:33:01,122
I got really stressed about the number eight.

873
00:33:01,123 --> 00:33:02,663
- Right.
- So this time, I wanted...

874
00:33:03,023 --> 00:33:05,492
- to break free from the number.
- You broke free.

875
00:33:05,493 --> 00:33:06,902
- So I joined the show for that too.
- Right.

876
00:33:06,903 --> 00:33:08,932
- Eighth and eighth.
- Congratulations.

877
00:33:08,933 --> 00:33:10,132
- Eighth and eighth.
- So,

878
00:33:10,133 --> 00:33:11,772
Ji Yun said...

879
00:33:11,773 --> 00:33:14,142
people told her,

880
00:33:14,143 --> 00:33:15,672
"It must be frustrating that you were in second place."

881
00:33:15,673 --> 00:33:17,642
In my case,

882
00:33:17,643 --> 00:33:19,013
people keep telling me,

883
00:33:19,273 --> 00:33:21,682
"What a shame. I really voted for you a lot,"

884
00:33:21,683 --> 00:33:23,142
"but you were in eighth place."

885
00:33:23,143 --> 00:33:25,312
- I heard that so many times.
- Right.

886
00:33:25,313 --> 00:33:27,152
- That made me more determined.
- No wonder...

887
00:33:27,153 --> 00:33:28,782
- you got addicted to auditions.
- That's right.

888
00:33:28,783 --> 00:33:31,353
- This also...
- But if I placed 8th 2 times...

889
00:33:31,853 --> 00:33:33,292
in auditions that picked the top seven,

890
00:33:33,293 --> 00:33:34,822
- I'd also do it again.
- That's right.

891
00:33:34,823 --> 00:33:35,922
- Right.
- In frustration.

892
00:33:35,923 --> 00:33:37,662
That's right. You were so close.

893
00:33:37,663 --> 00:33:40,502
How did you decide to sing trot music?

894
00:33:40,503 --> 00:33:43,902
- Right.
- Ever since I was in middle school,

895
00:33:43,903 --> 00:33:45,902
so many people told me I looked like Jang Yun Jung.

896
00:33:45,903 --> 00:33:46,903
That's right.

897
00:33:46,904 --> 00:33:48,802
- My side profile.
- Jang Yun Jung?

898
00:33:48,803 --> 00:33:50,512
- I can see that.
- So,

899
00:33:50,513 --> 00:33:53,612
as a joke, whenever I went to karaokes, I sang trot songs.

900
00:33:53,613 --> 00:33:56,012
My parents also told me I sang trot songs well.

901
00:33:56,013 --> 00:33:58,482
So I thought singing trot songs...

902
00:33:58,483 --> 00:34:01,052
and enjoying that was my talent.

903
00:34:01,053 --> 00:34:03,452
I also sang many trot songs when I was an idol group member.

904
00:34:03,453 --> 00:34:06,122
I sang them a lot on radio shows...

905
00:34:06,123 --> 00:34:07,762
- or "Challenge 1000 Songs."
- "Challenge 1000 Songs."

906
00:34:07,763 --> 00:34:08,922
- "Challenge 1000 Songs."
- Her age...

907
00:34:08,923 --> 00:34:10,462
You can tell which generation she's from.

908
00:34:10,463 --> 00:34:11,762
We can tell Solji's as well.

909
00:34:11,763 --> 00:34:13,062
Do you know "Challenge 1000 Songs?"

910
00:34:13,063 --> 00:34:14,202
- I don't.
- What's happening?

911
00:34:14,203 --> 00:34:15,662
It was a show hosted by Jang Yun Jung.

912
00:34:15,663 --> 00:34:16,832
That's right.

913
00:34:16,833 --> 00:34:21,402
My agency's CEO saw me sing trot songs then...

914
00:34:21,403 --> 00:34:22,502
and scouted me.

915
00:34:22,503 --> 00:34:25,243
- That's nice.
- So I transitioned very naturally.

916
00:34:25,513 --> 00:34:28,242
You tried multiple times and finally made it in the end.

917
00:34:28,243 --> 00:34:30,412
I heard there's a song that gave you wings.

918
00:34:30,413 --> 00:34:31,413
Really?

919
00:34:31,414 --> 00:34:33,482
That's right. It's a song I sang in the preliminaries.

920
00:34:33,483 --> 00:34:36,452
- It was "Wings" by Heo Young Ran.
- "Wings."

921
00:34:36,453 --> 00:34:38,652
As I kept trying out the auditions,

922
00:34:38,653 --> 00:34:41,022
I thought a lot...

923
00:34:41,023 --> 00:34:42,792
about what song I should sing in the first round...

924
00:34:42,793 --> 00:34:44,762
to really express my true feelings.

925
00:34:44,763 --> 00:34:48,133
I was also in a position where I could have been eliminated.

926
00:34:48,603 --> 00:34:49,932
- I thought...
- It was a song you sang...

927
00:34:49,933 --> 00:34:51,202
when you were troubled.

928
00:34:51,203 --> 00:34:52,302
- You were feeling troubled.
- Right.

929
00:34:52,303 --> 00:34:55,372
I cried so much after listening to the song.

930
00:34:55,373 --> 00:34:58,213
The lyrics are about getting up and running again.

931
00:34:58,613 --> 00:35:01,142
- It's about youth.
- I see. Please sing that for us.

932
00:35:01,143 --> 00:35:04,682
I sang that song sincerely,

933
00:35:04,683 --> 00:35:06,652
and I got to advance to the next round alone.

934
00:35:06,653 --> 00:35:08,082
Let's listen to "Wings" today.

935
00:35:08,083 --> 00:35:09,382
Please sing that for us.

936
00:35:09,383 --> 00:35:11,692
- "Wings."
- I remember it.

937
00:35:11,693 --> 00:35:12,893
Let's go!

938
00:35:13,593 --> 00:35:19,733
("Wings," the song that freed her from the curse of 8th place)

939
00:35:21,563 --> 00:35:25,703
("Wings" by Kang Hye Yeon, original song by Heo Young Ran)

940
00:36:12,683 --> 00:36:16,352
(Get up)

941
00:36:16,353 --> 00:36:19,693
(And run)

942
00:36:23,693 --> 00:36:27,063
(Fly)

943
00:36:33,503 --> 00:36:34,603
It's so nice.

944
00:37:12,473 --> 00:37:16,313
(She grew wings and evolved into a trot flying squirrel.)

945
00:37:16,683 --> 00:37:19,782
It was so nice.

946
00:37:19,783 --> 00:37:22,122
- It was the best.
- You didn't play the AR, right?

947
00:37:22,123 --> 00:37:23,582
- I didn't.
- We talked about that.

948
00:37:23,583 --> 00:37:25,322
- We thought the AR was playing.
- Seriously.

949
00:37:25,323 --> 00:37:27,093
After Yim Jae Beom...

950
00:37:27,393 --> 00:37:29,362
After "You" by Yim Jae Beom,

951
00:37:29,363 --> 00:37:30,662
"Wings" by Hye Yeon...

952
00:37:30,663 --> 00:37:32,092
seems like it will become a song that comforts...

953
00:37:32,093 --> 00:37:33,532
those going through hard times.

954
00:37:33,533 --> 00:37:34,533
The songs in between...

955
00:37:34,534 --> 00:37:36,732
Is he Lim Jin Mo?

956
00:37:36,733 --> 00:37:38,332
Judge Lee Sang Min's...

957
00:37:38,333 --> 00:37:40,273
- comment...
- Indebted Jin Mo.

958
00:37:40,673 --> 00:37:42,402
Behind the scenes of "The King of Active Trot Singers 3."

959
00:37:42,403 --> 00:37:45,073
Following "winning" and "challenge," we have "meeting."

960
00:37:45,143 --> 00:37:46,342
Our meeting

961
00:37:46,343 --> 00:37:49,082
What meeting are you talking about?

962
00:37:49,083 --> 00:37:50,343
I heard Su Yeon...

963
00:37:50,513 --> 00:37:52,552
dreamed about becoming a singer...

964
00:37:52,553 --> 00:37:54,622
after seeing Ji Yun sing.

965
