1442
00:56:26,584 --> 00:56:29,583
- So I try not to wash myself.
- You don't wash yourself?

1443
00:56:29,584 --> 00:56:30,783
When there's something important...

1444
00:56:30,784 --> 00:56:33,183
You know, they say the washing makes good luck run away.

1445
00:56:33,184 --> 00:56:34,583
There are people who don't wash their hair before exams.

1446
00:56:34,584 --> 00:56:36,153
And they don't clip their nails.

1447
00:56:36,154 --> 00:56:37,193
- Right.
- And toenails.

1448
00:56:37,194 --> 00:56:38,593
- I tend to be like that.
- I thought...

1449
00:56:38,594 --> 00:56:39,994
- you stank today.
- Someone doesn't dye their hair.

1450
00:56:41,194 --> 00:56:42,463
- Jang Hoon wouldn't like that.
- Did she stink?

1451
00:56:42,464 --> 00:56:44,733
- Right.
- About seaweed soup...

1452
00:56:44,734 --> 00:56:46,564
While entering "The King of Active Trot Singers,"

1453
00:56:47,104 --> 00:56:48,673
my mom didn't cook seaweed soup at all.

1454
00:56:48,674 --> 00:56:50,703
My birthday was in January,

1455
00:56:50,704 --> 00:56:52,103
but she didn't cook seaweed soup...

1456
00:56:52,104 --> 00:56:53,773
because I was in the middle of a competition.

1457
00:56:53,774 --> 00:56:54,774
- It's shamanism.
- So I couldn't eat it.

1458
00:56:54,775 --> 00:56:55,873
You couldn't eat it.

1459
00:56:55,874 --> 00:56:58,444
I do believe in superstitions.

1460
00:56:58,644 --> 00:57:02,453
There was something in my car that I wanted to throw away,

1461
00:57:02,454 --> 00:57:05,823
but my mom said we should throw it out after the competition,

1462
00:57:05,824 --> 00:57:07,453
so I couldn't bring myself to throw it away.

1463
00:57:07,454 --> 00:57:10,293
I can't even imagine eating seaweed soup.

1464
00:57:10,294 --> 00:57:11,963
- Really?
- She believes in stuff like that.

1465
00:57:11,964 --> 00:57:13,123
- For me...
- Superstitions.

1466
00:57:13,124 --> 00:57:15,294
Unlike Su Yeon, I'm extremely superstitious.

1467
00:57:15,564 --> 00:57:17,063
So, before the competition,

1468
00:57:17,064 --> 00:57:18,903
I went to get my fortune read.

1469
00:57:18,904 --> 00:57:20,003
I went to a fortune-teller and said,

1470
00:57:20,004 --> 00:57:22,333
"I really need to make it into the Top Seven."

1471
00:57:22,334 --> 00:57:24,003
"Is there anything..."

1472
00:57:24,004 --> 00:57:26,503
- "reassuring, like a talisman?"
- A talisman?

1473
00:57:26,504 --> 00:57:28,313
Then the fortune-teller said,

1474
00:57:28,314 --> 00:57:29,443
"Since your energy is weak,"

1475
00:57:29,444 --> 00:57:31,173
"you have to eat pork the day before the competition."

1476
00:57:31,174 --> 00:57:33,513
So I made sure to eat pork...

1477
00:57:33,514 --> 00:57:35,013
- the day before the competition.
- It must've been delicious.

1478
00:57:35,014 --> 00:57:36,813
- Really?
- What about you, Su Yeon?

1479
00:57:36,814 --> 00:57:38,784
I understand why Hye Yeon felt that way.

1480
00:57:38,924 --> 00:57:40,724
When you keep coming in eighth place,

1481
00:57:41,084 --> 00:57:42,153
- you start wanting...
- I understand her.

1482
00:57:42,154 --> 00:57:43,394
- to rely on something.
- That's how you feel.

1483
00:57:43,494 --> 00:57:45,824
So, they specifically told you to eat pork?

1484
00:57:46,064 --> 00:57:47,393
- Did they say it would work?
- Does the fortune-teller...

1485
00:57:47,394 --> 00:57:48,633
run a butcher shop?

1486
00:57:48,634 --> 00:57:49,664
What? A butcher shop?

1487
00:57:50,494 --> 00:57:52,103
"You should go to a butcher shop over there."

1488
00:57:52,104 --> 00:57:54,864
- You have to go to the shop I pick.
- It would've been better with beef.

1489
00:57:55,004 --> 00:57:57,303
Apparently, pork is better for my constitution than beef.

1490
00:57:57,304 --> 00:57:58,973
- Your constitution?
- That's safer.

1491
00:57:58,974 --> 00:58:01,143
Let's go. Solji, Tae Yeon, and Hye Yeon.

1492
00:58:01,144 --> 00:58:03,713
Now, Solji, Tae Yeon, and Hye Yeon...

1493
00:58:03,714 --> 00:58:05,484
